            },
            "answer_text": "Probably the best thing to prevent a volcano from erupting with devastating force would be to drill holes. This would encourage minor eruptions and allow lava chambers to lower the pressure.  If you ever shaken a bottle with fizz and uncorked/opened it then you do quickly realize that just letting off steam is not exactly what is happening. Lava almost always contains high pressure gas which will fizz much like a shaken bottle. Clearly the drilling team would have to consist of heroes.  The reason why this solution has been proposed and yet never been done yet is similar to why earthquakes are not prevented. There a fairly good understanding how to do that: inject lubricants / water directly in the fault lines. This would allow the earth to un-stress in a much softer way and induce a large amount of minor shocks. While this method would work it would instant cause trillions of dollar court cases because the direct correlation of humans doing something and property being damaged. Lets not forget that last year in Italy a team trying to predict a earthquake went to jail for failing to be able to pinpoint the day and time. (Scientists convicted of manslaughter for failing to warn of earthquake ) ",
